The paper focuses on software engineering and specifically on identifying patterns in violations and their fixes. This suggests that cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category. The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests a possible fit with cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also involves evaluating the usefulness of identified fix patterns, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
